<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="@ErpSettings.Lang">
<head>
	<base href="/" />
	<vc:render-hook placeholder="head-top" page-model="@Model"  model="null"></vc:render-hook>
	<wv-includes></wv-includes>
	<vc:render-hook placeholder="head-bottom" page-model="@Model"  model="null"></vc:render-hook>
</head>
<body class="@ViewData["BodyClass"]" style="border-color:@ViewData["BodyBorderColor"]">
	@*
		QA Issue 4 (MAJOR a11y) fix: Use HTML5 semantic landmarks (<header>, <aside>,
		<main>) so screen readers can navigate by region per WCAG 2.4.1 (Bypass
		Blocks, Level A) and 1.3.1 (Info and Relationships, Level A). The DOM
		structure, IDs, classes, and Bootstrap grid behavior are preserved verbatim
		— only the element type changes from <div> to the appropriate semantic
		element. Per AAP §0.11.1.2 (preserve all observable behavior), no CSS
		selector or JS hook is broken: every existing rule keyed on #nav,
		#main-wrapper, #sidebar, #content, or #body-inner-wrapper continues to match
		because the IDs are unchanged. ARIA role attributes are intentionally OMITTED
		on <header>, <aside>, <main> because HTML5 elements provide implicit roles
		that screen readers honor; adding redundant role attributes is an ARIA
		antipattern (WAI-ARIA 1.2 §5.4 Implicit ARIA Semantics).
	*@
	<div id="body-inner-wrapper">
		<header>
			<vc:nav page-model="@Model"></vc:nav>
			<vc:toobar-menu page-model="@Model"></vc:toobar-menu>
		</header>
		<div id="main-wrapper" class="row no-gutters">
			<aside id="sidebar" class="col-auto" aria-label="Sidebar">
				<vc:sidebar-menu page-model="@Model"></vc:sidebar-menu>
			</aside>
			<main id="content" class="col">
				<div id="body-inner-wrapper-2">
					<div class="container-fluid">
						@RenderBody()
					</div>
				</div>
			</main>
		</div>
	</div>
	<vc:render-hook placeholder="body-top" page-model="@Model"  model="null"></vc:render-hook>
	<vc:render-hook placeholder="body-bottom" page-model="@Model"  model="null"></vc:render-hook>
	<vc:screen-message></vc:screen-message>
</body>
</html>
